&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity to advance your skills and knowledge within the Safeguarding and Protecting children; Adults with care and support needs and Looked after Children agendas&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications: BSc Specialist practitioner &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; (Or equivalent Nursing /Social Care qualification)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;East Lancashire and Blackburn with Darwen CCGs are seeking to appoint a specialist safeguarding practitioner which will be supported by the Pennine Lancashire CCG Safeguarding team and Heads of Safeguarding to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure Critical services are in place to respond to requirements to support those at risk of harm&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure delivery of improved outcomes for the most vulnerable in society, including all types of vulnerable adult abuse, looked after children and care leavers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Primary Care, health and social care and multiagency providers to ensure that pathways, procedures and the competency of the workforce are effective in protecting those at risk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative and integrated working with other statutory and voluntary agencies and partners to ensure the safe delivery of effective safeguarding systems and processes to support those who are deemed at risk of harm, abuse or are deemed vulnerable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead on key safeguarding portfolios and support across a range of all age safeguarding work streams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers great challenges for you, as a highly motivated and energetic individual to make a positive contribution to the outcomes for this group of vulnerable children and adults.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameCaroline WaldronEmail addressCaroline.waldron3@nhs.netTelephone number01282 644987Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
